                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60f 2/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-24T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1923—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Your 38, October 11, 3 p.m. Signatures of notes Saturday or Monday next.
                    Inasmuch as provisions cannot by law become effective here until after formal
                    approval by Council of Ministers and publication Department’s text will be
                    changed so as to make most-favored-nation treatment operative November 5, 1923,
                    instead of “on the day on which the exchange of notes is consummated”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
